The province’s fire season officially started on June 1. The Lowveld and Escarpment Fire Protection Association (Lefpa) launched this season last Friday along with opening its new offices at the Nelspruit Airfield. ALSO READ: City of Mbombela slow to act on illegal dumping in White River “We were in town and then said it was time to come back home again, here where the action is, where the planes are,” said the Lefpa manager, André Scheepers, about returning to the place at which they had been based previously. The day consisted of various talks by role players in the industry as well as the occasional fly-by demonstrations. ALSO READ: City of Mbombela Local Municipality needs R214m to upgrade the current electrical infrastructure It was an opportunity for industry companies to introduce themselves to Lefpa members and the public. With the Lowveld Aero Club also having its open day at the same time, refreshments were served at the club for any attendees of the launch. Scheepers said the launch day and all it had to offer exceeded his expectations and the event was well supported. 